author: Written by: FOX8Live.com Staff
title: You gotta be kitten me! #WhoCat becomes viral sensation
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - There was a cat in the Superdome during the Saints 31-21 victory over the Falcons. I mean, cats don't like birds, right? It only seemed logical.
OMG. It's a real cat ?? #wtf pic.twitter.com/LtsQAQjqxP
— Julie Couret (@JCWilloz) October 16, 2015 This raised questions among the Black and Gold faithful.
HOW IS THERE AN ACTUAL CAT HANGING OUT AT THE SUPERDOME IN A VERA BRADLEY BAG.
— lMn (@_MidwestMess) October 16, 2015 @JCWilloz @nflcatwatch Cats in the dome. Saints win. Coincidence?
— Ganondward (@Ganondward) October 16, 2015 It led to clever puns.
. @JCWilloz @cmadmax I think we can genuinely say here: The cat is out of the bag.
— Lee in Iowa (@Lee_in_Iowa) October 16, 2015 Journalists stopped what they were doing to get answers.
Ran all the way to Section 624 but the cat is gone. Folks in the section say it's a service animal, guy got off flight, cat was freaked.
— Jason Saul (@jasonmsaul) October 16, 2015 And it possibly sparked a new tradition.
@JCWilloz if Saints can hold on and win tonight this cat is coming to every game
— Balki Bartokomous (@wargote4) October 16, 2015 And in true social media form, #WhoCat is trending in New Orleans the day after the game.
